President Obama met with Ambassador Stephen Bosworth, the newly appointed Special Representative for North Korea Policy. The meeting was held to discuss the issue of North Korea's nuclear and missile programs. At the request of the President and Secretary of State, Ambassador Bosworth will be traveling next week to consult with allies and partners in the Six-Party Talks. Ambassador Bosworth has previously served as the United States Ambassador to the Republic of Korea, Executive Director of the Korean Peninsula Energy Development Organization, and Ambassador to Tunisia and the Philippines. He currently serves as the Dean of the Fletcher School of Law and Diplomacy at Tufts University.